These notes made while performing a [[RHEL]] 3 kernel upgrade from version 2.4.21-50.EL to 2.4.21-51.EL.

In the command snippets below <tt>$</tt> is a normal prompt and <tt>#</tt> is a superuser prompt.

= Preliminaries =

Do everything inside a [[screen]] session in case we lose the connection:

<pre>$ screen</pre>

As basically every operation requires root privileges, do this in a root shell rather than using [[sudo]] for every command:

<pre>$ sudo -s</pre>

